    {
      "content": "MongoDB is an open-source document database that provides high performance, high availability, and automatic scaling.",
      "pos": [
        603,
        720
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "MongoDB can be installed as a stand-alone database or within a cluster, leveraging built-in replication capabilities.",
      "pos": [
        721,
        838
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In some cases, you can use replication to increase read capacity.",
      "pos": [
        839,
        904
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Clients have the ability to send read and write operations to different servers.",
      "pos": [
        905,
        985
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can also maintain copies in different data centers to increase the locality and availability of data for distributed applications.",
      "pos": [
        986,
        1120
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "With MongoDB, replication also provides redundancy and increases data availability.",
      "pos": [
        1121,
        1204
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "With multiple copies of data on different database servers, replication protects a database from the loss of a single server.",
      "pos": [
        1205,
        1330
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Replication also allows you to recover from hardware failure and service interruptions.",
      "pos": [
        1331,
        1418
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "With additional copies of the data, you can dedicate one to disaster recovery, reporting, or backup.",
      "pos": [
        1419,
        1519
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        1521,
        1825
      ],
      "content": "In addition to the various flavors that were already available in the Azure Marketplace, now you can also easily deploy a new MongoDB cluster on Ubuntu VMs using a Azure Resource Manager template deployed through <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Azure PowerShell<ept id=\"p1\">](../powershell-install-configure.md)</ept> or the <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Azure CLI<ept id=\"p2\">](../xplat-cli.md)</ept>."
    },
    {
